What you need to know:

It was a swift and sweet revenge by the 24-year-old Kandie against Kiplimo, who beat him at the World Half Marathon Championships in Gdynia, in Poland on October 17 this yearKandie’s victory and the world rceord saw him pocket a total of Sh18.09million; 35,000 Euros (Sh 4.69million) for winning and a bonus of 100,000 Euros (Sh 13.4 million) for breaking the world recordIn the women’s race, Ethiopian Genzebe Dibaba became the fastest debutant over the distance when she won the women’s race in 1:05:18, beating Kenya’s Sheila Chepkirui to second place in 1:05:39